01:03:31,234 --> 01:03:35,490
But would she see through the bars
of his plight and ache for him?

743
01:03:35,554 --> 01:03:37,758
Please keep that.
I couldn't.

744
01:03:37,826 --> 01:03:39,353
I insist.

745
01:03:49,442 --> 01:03:50,554
Good-bye.

746
01:03:52,066 --> 01:03:54,881
Let's get something to eat.
Of course.

747
01:03:54,946 --> 01:03:56,801
Why not?

748
01:04:27,970 --> 01:04:29,880
Is that you, Doctor?

749
01:05:18,562 --> 01:05:21,431
I'd like to speak with
Chief Inspector Rinaldo Pazzi, please.

750
01:05:21,506 --> 01:05:24,605
This is Agent Clarice Starling
from the American FBI.

751
01:05:24,674 --> 01:05:25,917
One moment.

752
01:05:28,386 --> 01:05:31,201
FBI.
I'm not here.

753
01:05:35,842 --> 01:05:36,954
Inspector Pazzi.

754
01:05:37,026 --> 01:05:39,776
It's Agent Starling
from the FBI. How do you do?

755
01:05:39,842 --> 01:05:43,322
Actually, I was just
leaving for the day.

756
01:05:43,394 --> 01:05:45,434
Can I call you back tomorrow?
This won't take long.

757
01:05:45,506 --> 01:05:50,394
First, thank you for sending us the
security tape from the perfume store.

758
01:05:50,466 --> 01:05:53,979
When I say "you,"I mean
your department... Agent Benetti.

759
01:05:54,050 --> 01:05:57,116
Is he there?
Can I speak with him?

760
01:05:57,186 --> 01:06:00,001
I'm sorry. He's gone home.
That's all right.

761
01:06:00,066 --> 01:06:02,237
I should tell you this
rather than him anyway.

762
01:06:02,306 --> 01:06:04,543
I'm late for
an important appointment.

763
01:06:04,610 --> 01:06:07,130
The person I'm looking for,
Inspector...

764
01:06:07,202 --> 01:06:10,072
who is indeed shown on that tape,
is Hannibal Lecter.

765
01:06:10,145 --> 01:06:11,672
Who?

766
01:06:11,746 --> 01:06:14,561
Dr. Hannibal Lecter.
You've never heard of him?

767
01:06:14,626 --> 01:06:18,238
I'm not familiar.
And the tape confirms...

768
01:06:18,306 --> 01:06:20,794
that he is
or was recently in Florence.

769
01:06:22,434 --> 01:06:25,336
Really?
He's a very dangerous man, Inspector.

770
01:06:25,410 --> 01:06:28,639
He's killed 14 people
that we know of.

771
01:06:28,706 --> 01:06:30,975
I really have to go, Miss...
Starling.

772
01:06:31,042 --> 01:06:32,635
Just another minute.

773
01:06:32,706 --> 01:06:35,521
You sure you've never heard of him?
No, I haven't.

774
01:06:35,586 --> 01:06:37,441
Because I'm confused.

775
01:06:37,506 --> 01:06:41,761
Someone there has been accessing
our private VICAP files on Dr. Lecter...

776
01:06:41,825 --> 01:06:44,728
with some regularity
on your computer.

777
01:06:44,801 --> 01:06:48,576
Everybody uses
everybody's computer here.

778
01:06:48,641 --> 01:06:51,456
Maybe one of the detectives
on II Mostro...

779
01:06:51,521 --> 01:06:53,409
was looking at
profiles of killers...

780
01:06:53,474 --> 01:06:55,841
I'm speaking about the computer
at your home, sir.

781
01:06:57,346 --> 01:07:00,695
You're trying to catch him yourself,
aren't you? For the reward.

782
01:07:00,769 --> 01:07:03,257
I cannot warn you
strongly enough against that.

783
01:07:03,330 --> 01:07:06,080
He killed three policemen
down in Memphis while in custody...

784
01:07:06,146 --> 01:07:09,724
tearing the face off one of them,
and he will kill you too.

785
01:07:43,074 --> 01:07:46,335
I want him out of Tuscany fast.
Believe me...

786
01:07:46,401 --> 01:07:49,249
he'll be gone
from the face of the earth fast.

787
01:07:49,314 --> 01:07:50,841
Feetfirst.

788
01:08:09,826 --> 01:08:13,241
Because of his avarice and his betrayal
of the emperor's trust...

789
01:08:13,314 --> 01:08:17,405
Pier della Vigna was disgraced,
blinded and imprisoned.

790
01:08:17,473 --> 01:08:22,841
Dante's pilgrim finds Pier della Vigna
on the seventh level of the Inferno...

791
01:08:22,914 --> 01:08:26,230
and, likeJudas Iscariot,
he died by hanging.

792
01:08:26,306 --> 01:08:29,056
SoJudas and Pier della Vigna
are linked in Dante...

793
01:08:29,122 --> 01:08:31,358
by the avarice
he saw in them.

794
01:08:31,425 --> 01:08:35,616
In fact, avarice and hanging
are linked in the medieval mind.

795
01:08:35,682 --> 01:08:38,943
This is the earliest known
depiction of the Crucifixion...

796
01:08:39,010 --> 01:08:43,133
carved on an ivory box in Gaul
about A.D. 400.

797
01:08:43,202 --> 01:08:47,839
It includes the death
by hanging ofJudas...

798
01:08:47,906 --> 01:08:49,760
his face upturned
to the branch that suspends him.

799
01:08:49,826 --> 01:08:52,695
Here he is again on the doors
of the Benevento Cathedral...

800
01:08:52,770 --> 01:08:56,479
this time
with his bowels falling out.

801
01:09:03,330 --> 01:09:06,526
It wasn't easy, but I got this number
without tellin'them why...

802
01:09:06,593 --> 01:09:08,895
Sorry.
Not at all. Welcome.

803
01:09:08,961 --> 01:09:12,158
Please join us.
Thank you.

804
01:09:12,226 --> 01:09:15,041
On this plate from the
15th-century edition of the Inferno...

805
01:09:15,106 --> 01:09:18,488
Pier della Vigna's body
hangs from a bleeding tree.

806
01:09:18,561 --> 01:09:21,376
I will not belabor the obvious
parallel with Judas Iscariot...

807
01:09:21,441 --> 01:09:24,256
but Dante Alighieri
needed no drawn illustration.

808
01:09:24,321 --> 01:09:28,729
It was his genius to make
Pier della Vigna, now in hell...

809
01:09:28,802 --> 01:09:31,617
speak in strained hisses
and coughing sibilants...

810
01:09:31,682 --> 01:09:34,432
as though
he is hanging still.

811
01:09:58,114 --> 01:10:00,383
Avarice, hanging...

812
01:10:00,449 --> 01:10:01,944
self-destruction.

813
01:10:06,146 --> 01:10:08,285
"I make my own home...

814
01:10:09,314 --> 01:10:11,169
be my gallows."

815
01:10:12,546 --> 01:10:15,579
Thank you, ladies and gentlemen,
for your kind attention.

816
01:10:30,913 --> 01:10:33,913
I'm not a scholar,
but I think you've got the job.

817
01:10:33,986 --> 01:10:35,196
Thank you.

818
01:10:35,265 --> 01:10:38,080
May I buy you a drink?
How kind of you. I'd like that.

819
01:10:38,145 --> 01:10:40,960
I'll be a minute
gathering my things.

820
01:10:41,025 --> 01:10:42,935
Take your time.

821
01:10:52,162 --> 01:10:56,155
Allegra, I'll be home
just a little later than I said.

822
01:10:56,225 --> 01:10:58,135
I'm taking Dr. Fell out
for a drink.

823
01:11:01,633 --> 01:11:03,673
I can see the people
coming out now.

824
01:11:05,825 --> 01:11:08,411
Yes. Bye, honey. My wife.

825
01:11:08,482 --> 01:11:10,042
Of course.

826
01:11:12,353 --> 01:11:14,939
I should have shown them
this one.

827
01:11:15,010 --> 01:11:18,654
I can't imagine how I missed it.
Remember? I told you about it.

828
01:11:18,721 --> 01:11:21,242
It's a rendering
I found in the Capponi Library.

829
01:11:21,314 --> 01:11:23,964
Can you make it out?

830
01:11:24,034 --> 01:11:26,684
There's a name there...

831
01:11:26,753 --> 01:11:28,761
the one I told you about.

832
01:11:41,249 --> 01:11:43,289
It's your ancestor,
Commendatore...

833
01:11:43,361 --> 01:11:45,849
hanging beneath
these very windows.

834
01:11:45,922 --> 01:11:47,710
Francesco de' Pazzi.

835
01:11:48,929 --> 01:11:52,377
On a related subject,
I must confess to you...

836
01:11:52,450 --> 01:11:54,905
I'm giving very serious thought...

837
01:12:00,770 --> 01:12:02,679
to eating your wife.

838
01:12:34,626 --> 01:12:37,528
If you tell me what I need to know,
Commendatore...

839
01:12:37,601 --> 01:12:40,089
it might be convenient for me
to leave Florence without my meal.

840
01:12:40,161 --> 01:12:43,609
So I'll ask you the questions,
and then we'll see. All right?

841
01:12:43,682 --> 01:12:44,958
Okay?

842
01:12:57,026 --> 01:12:58,236
So.

843
01:13:00,833 --> 01:13:03,168
Now, is it Mason Verger
you sold me to?

844
01:13:05,281 --> 01:13:06,775
No, no.

845
01:13:06,849 --> 01:13:08,954
Blink twice for yes,
once for no.

846
01:13:09,025 --> 01:13:11,481
Was it Mason Verger
you sold me to?

847
01:13:13,026 --> 01:13:14,880
Yes, good. Thank you.

848
01:13:14,946 --> 01:13:17,760
And are his men
waiting for me outside?

849
01:13:19,425 --> 01:13:21,432
Was that a single blink?

850
01:13:21,505 --> 01:13:23,328
You're confused.

851
01:13:23,394 --> 01:13:27,355
Please don't be confused, because I may
have to fillet Signora Pazzi after all.

852
01:13:30,401 --> 01:13:32,768
Have you told anyone
in the questura about me?

853
01:13:34,241 --> 01:13:36,064
No, I thought not.

854
01:13:36,705 --> 01:13:39,640
Have you told Allegra?

855
01:13:42,049 --> 01:13:43,958
No? Are you sure?

856
01:13:45,922 --> 01:13:47,515
I believe you.

857
01:13:49,985 --> 01:13:52,287
Okeydokey, here we go.

858
01:13:58,562 --> 01:13:59,739
Okay.

859
01:14:01,282 --> 01:14:02,808
Your heart is really palpitating.

860
01:14:02,881 --> 01:14:05,663
Oh, it's not your heart.

861
01:14:07,554 --> 01:14:09,594
Shall I answer it?

862
01:14:11,842 --> 01:14:14,395
I've gone above you.
I've spoken to your section chief.

863
01:14:14,465 --> 01:14:17,116
Someday you'll thank me.
Or you won't. I don't care.

864
01:14:17,185 --> 01:14:19,454
You'll be alive.

865
01:14:19,522 --> 01:14:21,310
Inspector Pazzi?

866
01:14:22,241 --> 01:14:24,445
Is this Clarice?

867
01:14:24,513 --> 01:14:26,880
Hello, Clarice.

868
01:14:27,970 --> 01:14:29,758
I'm afraid I have
bad news for you.

869
01:14:29,825 --> 01:14:32,859
Is he dead?
Did you get my note?

870
01:14:32,929 --> 01:14:35,482
I hope you like the skin cream.
I had it specially made for you.

871
01:14:35,554 --> 01:14:37,409
Is he dead, Dr. Lecter?

872
01:14:37,474 --> 01:14:41,435
I would love nothing more in this world
than to be able to chat with you.

873
01:14:41,506 --> 01:14:44,572
Unfortunately, you've caught me
at an awkward moment.

874
01:14:44,642 --> 01:14:46,813
Please forgive me.

875
01:14:46,881 --> 01:14:48,539
See you around.

876
01:14:50,721 --> 01:14:52,630
An old friend.

877
01:14:56,481 --> 01:14:57,975
Okay, hold on.

878
01:14:59,650 --> 01:15:01,024
Here we go.

879
01:15:32,034 --> 01:15:35,994
I'll go around back!
Kill him if you have to!

880
01:15:39,073 --> 01:15:40,960
What's it to be?

881
01:15:41,026 --> 01:15:43,131
Bowels in or bowels out...

882
01:15:43,202 --> 01:15:45,111
likeJudas?

883
01:15:45,185 --> 01:15:46,974
Are you confused?

884
01:15:47,042 --> 01:15:49,759
I'll decide for you,
if you'll permit me.

885
01:17:00,321 --> 01:17:01,565
Good evening.

886
01:18:06,146 --> 01:18:08,601
Cordell...

887
01:18:08,674 --> 01:18:10,528
to you...

888
01:18:10,594 --> 01:18:13,823
does that look
like a wave good-bye...

889
01:18:15,073 --> 01:18:17,408
or hello?

890
01:19:00,705 --> 01:19:03,771
So, what do you think?

891
01:19:03,841 --> 01:19:08,730
Does Lecter want to fuck her
or kill her or eat her or what?

892
01:19:08,801 --> 01:19:11,288
Probably all three.

893
01:19:11,361 --> 01:19:13,882
Though I wouldn't want
to predict in what order.

894
01:19:15,393 --> 01:19:17,881
Here's what I think.

895
01:19:17,953 --> 01:19:21,881
No matter how Barney
might want to romanticize it...

896
01:19:21,953 --> 01:19:25,695
and make it
Beauty and the Beast...

897
01:19:25,761 --> 01:19:28,795
Lecter's object, as I know
from personal experience...

898
01:19:28,865 --> 01:19:31,003
has always been...

899
01:19:31,073 --> 01:19:33,113
degradation...

900
01:19:33,185 --> 01:19:35,356
and suffering.

901
01:19:35,425 --> 01:19:39,997
Get this damn thing off me.
I can't breathe in this thing.

902
01:19:42,465 --> 01:19:45,531
He comes in the guise
of a mentor...

903
01:19:45,601 --> 01:19:48,863
as he did with me and her.

904
01:19:48,929 --> 01:19:52,726
But it's distress that excites him.

905
01:19:52,801 --> 01:19:54,624
To draw him...

906
01:19:55,905 --> 01:19:58,239
she needs to be distressed.

907
01:20:00,929 --> 01:20:05,119
To make her attractive to him,
let him see her distressed.

908
01:20:07,169 --> 01:20:09,656
Let the damage he sees...

909
01:20:09,729 --> 01:20:12,599
suggest the damage
he could do.

910
01:20:21,569 --> 01:20:25,147
When the fox hears the rabbit scream,
he comes a-runnin'.

911
01:20:26,881 --> 01:20:28,790
But not to help.

912
01:20:28,865 --> 01:20:30,720
I don't understand.

913
01:20:30,785 --> 01:20:32,858
There's nothing
to understand, Paul.

914
01:20:32,929 --> 01:20:36,606
All you have to understand
is what it's worth to you.

915
01:20:36,673 --> 01:20:39,487
No, no, I don't understand
why she didn't turn this over.

916
01:20:39,553 --> 01:20:41,440
I mean, she's such
a straight arrow.

917
01:20:41,505 --> 01:20:44,767
She didn't turn it over
because she didn't receive it.

918
01:20:44,833 --> 01:20:46,808
She didn't receive it
because it was never sent.

919
01:20:46,881 --> 01:20:49,215
It was never sent because
Lecter didn't write it.

920
01:20:49,281 --> 01:20:51,736
He didn't write it
because I did.

921
01:20:56,833 --> 01:20:58,687
So, what do you think?

922
01:20:58,753 --> 01:21:02,048
You'd have been better off if
you'd never got her out of trouble.

923
01:21:02,113 --> 01:21:05,975
Oh, woulda, shoulda, coulda. I meant,
what do you think about the money?

924
01:21:06,049 --> 01:21:07,161
Five.

925
01:21:08,193 --> 01:21:12,449
Let's just toss it off, like "five."

926
01:21:12,513 --> 01:21:15,360
Let's say it
with the respect it deserves.

927
01:21:15,425 --> 01:21:18,294
Five hundred thousand dollars.

928
01:21:18,369 --> 01:21:20,157
That's better, but not much.

929
01:21:20,225 --> 01:21:22,559
Now, will it work?
It'll work.

930
01:21:22,625 --> 01:21:24,698
It won't be pretty.

931
01:21:24,768 --> 01:21:26,678
What ever is?

932
01:21:29,985 --> 01:21:32,090
Cocksucker.

933
01:21:32,161 --> 01:21:35,008
Never seen this before
in my life.

934
01:21:35,073 --> 01:21:39,296
Then how do you account for its being
found in your office, your basement?

935
01:21:39,361 --> 01:21:42,176
How do you want me to answer that,
Mr. Krendler?

936
01:21:42,241 --> 01:21:45,056
What possible reason
might I have to withhold it?

937
01:21:45,121 --> 01:21:48,253
Perhaps because of the nature
of its content.

938
01:21:48,321 --> 01:21:51,168
Reads to me like a love letter.

939
01:21:51,233 --> 01:21:54,200
Has it been tested for prints?
No prints on it. None on the last one.

940
01:21:54,273 --> 01:21:56,096
Handwriting analysis?

941
01:21:56,161 --> 01:21:59,641
"Did you ever think, Clarice, why
the philistines don't understand you?

942
01:21:59,713 --> 01:22:01,917
It's because you're the answer
to Samson's riddle.

943
01:22:01,985 --> 01:22:03,992
You are the honey in the lion."

944
01:22:04,065 --> 01:22:05,527
Sounds like him to me.

945
01:22:05,601 --> 01:22:09,724
Do you mean, like a homosexual?
Like a nut with a crush.

946
01:22:09,793 --> 01:22:11,102
Director Noonan,
I need to say something...

947
01:22:11,169 --> 01:22:13,558
Agent Starling, I am placing you
on administrative leave...

948
01:22:13,633 --> 01:22:17,659
till document analysis tells me
unequivocally a mistake's been made.

949
01:22:17,729 --> 01:22:20,795
In the meantime, you remain eligible
for insurance and medical benefits.

950
01:22:20,865 --> 01:22:23,832
Surrender your weapons and
your identification to Agent Pearsall.

951
01:22:36,830 --> 01:22:39,480
I want to say something.
I think I'm entitled.

952
01:22:39,549 --> 01:22:41,240
Go ahead.

953
01:22:41,310 --> 01:22:44,659
I think Mr. Mason Verger is
trying to capture Dr. Lecter...

954
01:22:44,734 --> 01:22:46,643
for the purposes
of personal revenge.

955
01:22:46,718 --> 01:22:49,140
I think Mr. Krendler
is in collusion with him...

956
01:22:49,214 --> 01:22:52,028
and wants the FBI's efforts against
Dr. Lecter to work for Mr. Verger.

957
01:22:52,094 --> 01:22:54,843
I think Mr. Krendler
is being paid to do this.

958
01:22:54,909 --> 01:22:58,488
Lucky you're not sworn here today.
Swear me! You swear too!

959
01:22:58,558 --> 01:23:01,208
Clarice,
if the evidence is lacking...

960
01:23:01,277 --> 01:23:03,798
you'll be entitled to full reinstatement
without prejudice...

961
01:23:03,870 --> 01:23:08,125
if you don't do or say
anything in the meantime...

962
01:23:08,190 --> 01:23:10,612
that would make that impossible.

963
01:23:10,814 --> 01:23:14,011
Relieved of field duty pending
an internal investigation...

964
01:23:14,078 --> 01:23:16,925
Special Agent Clarice Starling,
a ten-year veteran on the Bureau...

965
01:23:16,989 --> 01:23:18,964
began her career
with an assignment...

966
01:23:19,038 --> 01:23:21,045
to interview lethal madman
Hannibal Lecter.

967
01:23:21,118 --> 01:23:24,795
Earlier, we heard comments from Justice
Department spokesman Paul Krendler.

968
01:23:25,885 --> 01:23:29,017
Can you comment on theJustice
Department's decision this morning?

969
01:23:29,086 --> 01:23:33,014
The FBI and theJustice Department are
looking very carefully into the charges.

970
01:23:33,086 --> 01:23:35,322
And, yes, they are extremely serious.

971
01:23:35,390 --> 01:23:36,851
I'd like to add
a personal note, though.

972
01:23:36,926 --> 01:23:41,366
Starling's one of our best agents.
No, no, no, stay.

973
01:23:41,438 --> 01:23:45,300
I would be very surprised if these
accusations turn out to be true.

974
01:23:45,374 --> 01:23:48,690
Is theJustice Department and FBI
united in this decision?

975
01:23:48,765 --> 01:23:51,351
It's much too soon to condemn her...

976
01:24:34,749 --> 01:24:36,407
Good boy.

977
01:27:11,966 --> 01:27:14,267
I think she's nice.

978
01:27:14,334 --> 01:27:17,083
She's always been nice to me.
Polite.

979
01:27:17,149 --> 01:27:18,611
Don't you think?

980
01:27:18,686 --> 01:27:21,500
Do you know what
a roller pigeon is, Barney?

981
01:27:21,566 --> 01:27:23,802
Roller pigeons
climb high and fast...

982
01:27:23,869 --> 01:27:26,837
then roll over and fall
just as fast towards the Earth.

983
01:27:26,909 --> 01:27:30,139
There are shallow rollers
and there are deep rollers...

984
01:27:30,206 --> 01:27:33,501
but you can't breed two deep rollers,
or their young, their offspring...

985
01:27:33,565 --> 01:27:36,860
will roll all the way down,
hit and die.

986
01:27:36,926 --> 01:27:40,755
Agent Starling is a deep roller.

987
01:27:40,830 --> 01:27:43,645
Let's hope
one of her parents was not.

988
01:29:10,206 --> 01:29:12,540
The power in that battery
is low, Clarice.

989
01:29:12,605 --> 01:29:15,223
I would've changed it,
but I didn't want to wake you.

990
01:29:15,293 --> 01:29:19,450
Use the one in the charger. Hopefully,
the light on it is green by now.

991
01:29:19,517 --> 01:29:22,135
Because this is gonna be a long call
and I can't let you off...

992
01:29:22,205 --> 01:29:24,540
because even though
you've been stripped of your duties...

993
01:29:24,606 --> 01:29:27,770
I know you won't abandon them...
you'll try to put on a trace.

994
01:29:27,838 --> 01:29:31,318
So we'll disconnect long enough for you
to exchange the battery in the phone...

995
01:29:31,389 --> 01:29:33,331
for the one in the charger.

996
01:29:33,405 --> 01:29:36,274
Shall we say, three seconds?

997
01:29:36,349 --> 01:29:37,843
Are you ready?
Yes.

998
01:29:37,917 --> 01:29:38,845
Go.

999
01:29:44,158 --> 01:29:45,980
Very good.
Thank you.

1000
01:29:46,045 --> 01:29:48,860
Remember, Clarice, if you get caught
with a concealed, unlicensed firearm...

1001
01:29:48,925 --> 01:29:51,642
in the District of Columbia,
the penalty is very stiff.

1002
01:29:51,709 --> 01:29:55,157
But bring the guns if you have to.
Now get in your car.

1003
01:30:30,653 --> 01:30:32,824
The reason we're doing it
like this, Clarice...

1004
01:30:32,893 --> 01:30:36,755
is because I like to watch you
as we speak, with your eyes open.

1005
01:30:37,918 --> 01:30:41,398
No, it does not excite me.
It pleases me.

1006
01:30:41,469 --> 01:30:43,803
You have very shapely feet.

1007
01:30:46,845 --> 01:30:49,333
Where are we now?
Call it out.

1008
01:30:49,405 --> 01:30:51,128
Massachusetts Avenue.

1009
01:30:51,197 --> 01:30:53,020
Take it.

1010
01:30:53,085 --> 01:30:56,729
I thought, to begin with,
you might tell me how you're feeling.

1011
01:30:56,797 --> 01:30:57,725
About what?

1012
01:30:57,789 --> 01:31:00,571
The masters you serve
and how they've treated you.

1013
01:31:00,637 --> 01:31:03,255
Your career, such as it is.

1014
01:31:03,325 --> 01:31:05,148
Your life, Clarice.

1015
01:31:05,213 --> 01:31:07,100
I thought we might
talk about yours.

1016
01:31:07,165 --> 01:31:10,035
What's the next cross street?
Capitol Street.

1017
01:31:10,110 --> 01:31:14,201
In two blocks, make a left
into Union Station. Park.

1018
01:31:15,453 --> 01:31:17,788
My life? What is there
to say about mine?

1019
01:31:17,853 --> 01:31:20,820
I have been in a state of hibernation
for some time...

1020
01:31:20,893 --> 01:31:22,900
a little inactive.

1021
01:31:22,973 --> 01:31:26,137
But now I'm back home
and I'm very happy...

1022
01:31:26,205 --> 01:31:27,863
and very healthy.

1023
01:31:27,933 --> 01:31:32,123
You. It's you I'm worried about.
I'm fine.

1024
01:31:32,190 --> 01:31:34,907
No, you're certainly
not fine, Clarice.

1025
01:31:34,973 --> 01:31:37,558
You fell in love with the Bureau,
the institution...

1026
01:31:37,629 --> 01:31:40,891
only to discover, after giving it
everything you've got...

1027
01:31:40,957 --> 01:31:42,964
that it does not
love you back...

1028
01:31:43,037 --> 01:31:44,979
that, in fact, it resents you.

1029
01:31:45,053 --> 01:31:47,901
It resents you more than the husband
and children you gave up to it.

1030
01:31:47,965 --> 01:31:52,242
Why is that, do you think?
Why are you so resented?

1031
01:31:52,317 --> 01:31:54,684
Tell me.
Tell you?

1032
01:31:54,749 --> 01:31:56,342
God bless you.

1033
01:31:56,413 --> 01:31:58,202
Well, isn't it clear?

1034
01:31:59,869 --> 01:32:03,165
You serve the idea
of order, Clarice.

1035
01:32:03,229 --> 01:32:04,571
They don't.

1036
01:32:04,637 --> 01:32:08,085
You believe in the oath you took.
They don't.

1037
01:32:08,158 --> 01:32:12,380
You feel it is your duty
to protect the sheep. They don't.

1038
01:32:12,445 --> 01:32:14,485
They don't like you
because you're not like them.

1039
01:32:14,557 --> 01:32:16,696
They hate you and envy you.

1040
01:32:16,765 --> 01:32:20,377
They are weak, unruly
and believe in nothing.

1041
01:32:20,445 --> 01:32:22,900
Mason Verger wants to kill you,
Dr. Lecter.

1042
01:32:22,973 --> 01:32:25,624
Turn yourself in to me,
and I promise no one will hurt you.

1043
01:32:25,694 --> 01:32:29,076
Will you stay with me in my prison cell
and hold my hand, Clarice?

1044
01:32:29,149 --> 01:32:31,418
We could have some fun.

1045
01:32:31,485 --> 01:32:34,802
No, Mason Verger does not want to kill
me any more than I want to kill him.

1046
01:32:34,877 --> 01:32:38,652
He just wants to see me suffer
in some unimaginable way.

1047
01:32:38,717 --> 01:32:40,757
He is rather twisted,
you know.

1048
01:32:40,829 --> 01:32:43,218
Have you had the pleasure
of meeting him?

1049
01:32:43,293 --> 01:32:45,398
Face-to-face, so to speak?

1050
01:32:45,469 --> 01:32:47,324
Yes.

1051
01:32:47,389 --> 01:32:50,389
Attractive, isn't he?
Dr. Lecter?

1052
01:32:54,685 --> 01:32:56,595
Okay, back to you.

1053
01:32:56,670 --> 01:32:58,841
I want to know what it is
you think you will do...

1054
01:32:58,909 --> 01:33:02,138
now that everything you've ever cared
about has been taken away from you.

1055
01:33:02,205 --> 01:33:04,539
I don't know, Dr. Lecter.

1056
01:33:04,605 --> 01:33:07,322
Clarice, do you think you'll work
as a chambermaid...

1057
01:33:07,389 --> 01:33:10,040
at a motel on Route 66...

1058
01:33:10,110 --> 01:33:12,728
just like your mommy?

1059
01:33:21,597 --> 01:33:23,604
What are you thinking now?

1060
01:33:23,677 --> 01:33:27,539
Are you paying attention to me,
ex-Special Agent Starling?

1061
01:33:28,350 --> 01:33:31,546
Are you, by any chance,
trying to trace my whereabouts?

1062
01:33:35,453 --> 01:33:38,770
I'm being followed, Dr. Lecter.
I know. I've seen them.

1063
01:33:38,845 --> 01:33:41,627
And now you're in
a real dilemma, aren't you?

1064
01:33:41,693 --> 01:33:45,370
Do you continue to try to find me,
knowing that you are leading them to me?

1065
01:33:45,437 --> 01:33:48,917
Do you have so much faith in your
abilities that you honestly believe...

1066
01:33:48,989 --> 01:33:52,699
you can somehow simultaneously
arrest me and them?

1067
01:33:52,765 --> 01:33:56,562
It could get very messy, Clarice,
like the fish market.

1068
01:33:58,205 --> 01:34:00,758
What if I did it for you?
Did what?

1069
01:34:00,829 --> 01:34:04,245
Harmed them, Clarice,
the ones who have harmed you.

1070
01:34:04,317 --> 01:34:07,481
What if I made them
scream apologies?

1071
01:34:07,549 --> 01:34:09,491
No, I shouldn't even say it...

1072
01:34:09,565 --> 01:34:12,827
because you'll feel, with your
perfect grasp of right and wrong...

1073
01:34:12,893 --> 01:34:15,032
that you were somehow accompli.

1074
01:34:16,285 --> 01:34:17,714
Don't help me.

1075
01:34:19,165 --> 01:34:21,075
No, of course not.
Forget I said it.

1076
01:34:25,853 --> 01:34:28,536
Clarice, you were very,
very warm.

1077
01:34:28,605 --> 01:34:30,515
You were so close.

1078
01:34:34,557 --> 01:34:37,372
And now you're getting
colder again.

1079
01:34:37,437 --> 01:34:39,576
Yeah, warmer again.

1080
01:34:39,645 --> 01:34:43,638
Well, I think I've been generous
enough with you and the clues.

1081
01:34:43,709 --> 01:34:47,058
You're on your own now, Clarice.
Dr. Lecter.

1082
01:34:55,965 --> 01:34:58,583
Hope you like them, Clarice.
Ta-ta.

1083
01:35:27,293 --> 01:35:28,787
Go.

1084
01:35:44,637 --> 01:35:46,492
Get out of the way!

1085
01:35:57,597 --> 01:36:00,347
I know the first thing a hysteric
says is, "I am not a hysteric"...

1086
01:36:00,413 --> 01:36:03,577
but I am not a hysteric.
I am calm.

1087
01:36:03,645 --> 01:36:06,395
I'll ask you one time.
Think before you answer.

1088
01:36:07,613 --> 01:36:10,460
Think about every good thing
you ever did.

1089
01:36:10,525 --> 01:36:12,347
Think about what you swore.

1090
01:36:12,413 --> 01:36:15,576
Two men in a van,
a third driving, another man down.

1091
01:36:15,644 --> 01:36:18,100
They put him in the back.
I think it was Lecter.

1092
01:36:18,173 --> 01:36:21,402
I gave you a license, and I'm reporting
it to you again in front of witnesses.

1093
01:36:23,357 --> 01:36:24,917
All right.

1094
01:36:26,013 --> 01:36:27,922
I'll go with it as a kidnapping.

1095
01:36:28,573 --> 01:36:30,581
I'll send someone
with the local authorities...

1096
01:36:30,653 --> 01:36:32,856
if they'll let us on the property
without a warrant.

1097
01:36:32,924 --> 01:36:37,081
I should go. You could deputize me.
No. You're not going.

1098
01:36:37,149 --> 01:36:39,735
You're going home,
where you'll wait for me to call...

1099
01:36:39,805 --> 01:36:43,350
and tell you what,
if anything, we've found.

1100
01:36:44,605 --> 01:36:47,768
Thank Mr. Verger for letting us look
around. Sorry if we inconvenienced him.

1101
01:36:47,837 --> 01:36:49,844
He's always happy to see you.

1102
01:36:59,037 --> 01:37:01,012
Phone.

1103
01:37:01,085 --> 01:37:03,573
What number, please?

1104
01:37:03,644 --> 01:37:04,954
Carlo.

1105
01:37:12,445 --> 01:37:13,939
Give me one.

1106
01:37:18,365 --> 01:37:20,732
How is he?
Sleeping.

1107
01:37:20,797 --> 01:37:23,448
Bring him home.

1108
01:37:45,565 --> 01:37:48,881
You've reached Clarice Starling.
Please leave a message.

1109
01:37:48,957 --> 01:37:50,451
Pick up, Starling.

1110
01:37:50,525 --> 01:37:52,413
There was nothing out there.

1111
01:37:52,477 --> 01:37:54,811
I'm gonna say it again,
in case you didn't hear me.

1112
01:37:54,877 --> 01:37:58,652
You are not a law officer while
you're on suspension. You'reJoe Blow.

1113
01:37:59,773 --> 01:38:02,643
Hope for your sake
you're in the bathroom.

1114
01:38:40,189 --> 01:38:41,782
Hylochoerus...

1115
01:38:41,853 --> 01:38:44,886
meinertzhageni.

1116
01:38:44,956 --> 01:38:48,885
Ring any bells from
high school biology, Doctor?

1117
01:38:49,917 --> 01:38:51,771
No?

1118
01:38:51,837 --> 01:38:55,284
Well, I could list
its most conspicuous features...

1119
01:38:55,357 --> 01:38:58,008
if that would help
jog the memory.

1120
01:38:58,717 --> 01:39:01,532
Three pairs of incisors...

1121
01:39:01,597 --> 01:39:06,005
one pair of elongated canines...

1122
01:39:07,453 --> 01:39:10,649
three pairs of molars...

1123
01:39:10,717 --> 01:39:13,172
four pairs of premolars...

1124
01:39:13,244 --> 01:39:15,448
upper and lower...

1125
01:39:15,517 --> 01:39:20,252
for a total of 44 teeth.

1126
01:39:24,829 --> 01:39:29,531
The meal will begin with
an hors d'oeuvres tartare...

1127
01:39:30,909 --> 01:39:33,527
your feet.

1128
01:39:33,597 --> 01:39:35,539
The main course...
the rest of you...

1129
01:39:35,613 --> 01:39:39,126
won't be served
until seven hours later.

1130
01:39:39,197 --> 01:39:41,368
But during that time...

1131
01:39:41,437 --> 01:39:45,692
you'll be able to enjoy the effects
of the consumed appetizer...

1132
01:39:45,757 --> 01:39:49,052
with a full-bodied saline drip.

1133
01:39:51,005 --> 01:39:54,136
I guess you wish now...

1134
01:39:54,205 --> 01:39:56,660
you'd fed the rest of me
to the dogs.

1135
01:39:58,077 --> 01:40:00,019
No, Mason.

1136
01:40:00,605 --> 01:40:03,060
No, I much prefer you
the way you are.

1137
01:40:04,124 --> 01:40:05,553
So...

1138
01:40:07,133 --> 01:40:08,988
dinner at 8:00.

1139
01:40:35,677 --> 01:40:39,157
You will stay
for the evening's entertainment...

1140
01:40:39,229 --> 01:40:40,920
won't you, Cordell?

1141
01:40:40,989 --> 01:40:43,477
If it's all right with you...

1142
01:40:43,548 --> 01:40:46,199
I think I'd rather not.

1143
01:40:46,268 --> 01:40:48,373
Rather not...

1144
01:40:48,444 --> 01:40:51,128
or will not?

1145
01:42:49,885 --> 01:42:53,846
Your little brother must smell
almost as badly as you do by now.

1146
01:43:20,476 --> 01:43:22,713
Hold it!
Hands where I can see 'em!

1147
01:43:27,292 --> 01:43:28,569
Quiet!

1148
01:43:33,916 --> 01:43:36,371
What was that?

1149
01:43:36,444 --> 01:43:37,655
Cordell, quickly!

1150
01:43:37,725 --> 01:43:40,692
Get on your stomach.

1151
01:43:40,765 --> 01:43:42,291
Good evening, Clarice.

1152
01:43:42,364 --> 01:43:45,266
Just like old times.
Shut up.

1153
01:43:47,037 --> 01:43:49,208
Can you walk?
I can try.

1154
01:43:52,156 --> 01:43:53,618
You look well.

1155
01:43:53,693 --> 01:43:55,635
I'm gonna cut you loose.

1156
01:43:55,708 --> 01:43:58,807
If you touch me,
I'll shoot you.

1157
01:43:58,876 --> 01:44:01,975
Understood.
Do right and you'll live through this.

1158
01:44:02,045 --> 01:44:04,892
Spoken like a true Protestant.
Better hurry.

1159
01:44:04,956 --> 01:44:07,291
Things might go faster
if you hand me the knife.

1160
01:44:07,357 --> 01:44:09,724
There was a third
in the loft.

1161
01:44:09,788 --> 01:44:13,203
No, Clarice. Behind me.

1162
01:44:49,437 --> 01:44:53,015
Cordell, shoot him!
Get the gun and shoot him!

1163
01:44:53,084 --> 01:44:55,418
Go into the pen?
Yes!

1164
01:44:55,484 --> 01:44:57,656
No. I'm staying out of this.

1165
01:44:57,725 --> 01:45:01,554
You're involved, is what you are,
in all of it. Now do it!

1166
01:45:01,628 --> 01:45:02,643
No.
Yes!

1167
01:45:02,717 --> 01:45:05,684
Hey, Cordell,
why don't you push him in?

1168
01:45:05,757 --> 01:45:07,797
You can always say
it was me.

1169
01:46:49,852 --> 01:46:51,379
Mary, it's me.

1170
01:46:51,453 --> 01:46:54,965
I decided to take off early.
I'll be at my lake house all weekend.

1171
01:46:55,036 --> 01:46:57,655
I don't want any calls
forwarded either. Do you understand?

1172
01:46:57,725 --> 01:47:00,375
Whoever it is,
they can all wait. Okay?

1173
01:47:00,444 --> 01:47:04,154
Listen, it's 4th ofJuly,
for Christ's sake. Thank you.

1174
01:47:19,228 --> 01:47:21,138
What the fuck?

1175
01:47:30,812 --> 01:47:32,787
Good. You brought the wine.

1176
01:48:51,708 --> 01:48:56,181
One time I bet a friend I could hold
a lit firecracker in my hand...

1177
01:48:56,252 --> 01:48:57,943
longer than he could.

1178
01:48:58,012 --> 01:48:59,092
Can I guess?

1179
01:48:59,164 --> 01:49:02,906
You lost the bet, and he lost
a finger. Am I right?

1180
01:49:03,997 --> 01:49:06,331
This won't hurt a bit.

1181
01:49:12,284 --> 01:49:14,585
Are we expecting guests?

1182
01:49:45,404 --> 01:49:49,659
We've traced your call and units
will be there in about ten minutes.

1183
01:49:49,724 --> 01:49:52,855
If you can do it safely,
just get out of the house.

1184
01:49:52,924 --> 01:49:56,055
Otherwise,
stay on the phone with me.

1185
01:49:56,124 --> 01:49:57,499
Ma'am?

1186
01:49:57,564 --> 01:50:00,313
Are you there? Ma'am?

1187
01:50:15,868 --> 01:50:17,941
You need to make sure
they feel welcome.

1188
01:50:23,004 --> 01:50:26,517
Are those shallots?
And caper berries.

1189
01:50:29,404 --> 01:50:31,313
That butter smells wonderful.

1190
01:50:32,572 --> 01:50:34,677
You feeling hungry, Paul?

1191
01:50:34,748 --> 01:50:36,603
Very.

1192
01:50:41,628 --> 01:50:43,930
What's the main course?

1193
01:50:43,996 --> 01:50:47,411
You should never ask.
It spoils the surprise.

1194
01:50:47,484 --> 01:50:52,121
Clarice, what are you doing up?
You should be resting. Get back to bed.

1195
01:50:52,188 --> 01:50:54,163
I'm hungry.

1196
01:50:56,604 --> 01:50:59,288
Hello, Paul.
Paul, don't be rude.

1197
01:51:00,444 --> 01:51:03,314
Say, "Hello, Agent Starling."

1198
01:51:03,388 --> 01:51:06,684
Hello, Agent Starling.

1199
01:51:08,444 --> 01:51:10,353
I always wanted
to watch you eat.

1200
01:51:10,428 --> 01:51:15,316
What have you got in your hand?
Something to bash me on the head with?

1201
01:51:16,124 --> 01:51:18,513
Put it on the table.

1202
01:51:18,588 --> 01:51:19,897
Good girl.

1203
01:51:19,964 --> 01:51:22,135
Hey. That's mine.

1204
01:51:22,204 --> 01:51:23,862
Now sit down.

1205
01:51:26,044 --> 01:51:28,859
Hey, Clarice, love the dress.

1206
01:51:28,924 --> 01:51:30,931
It's beautiful.

1207
01:51:31,004 --> 01:51:33,143
What do you think, Paul?
Nice.

1208
01:51:34,204 --> 01:51:35,960
Nice.

1209
01:51:43,804 --> 01:51:47,100
Why don't you say grace, Paul?

1210
01:51:47,164 --> 01:51:49,498
Me?
Yeah.

1211
01:51:49,564 --> 01:51:51,157
Grace?
Sure.

1212
01:51:52,028 --> 01:51:53,938
Okay.

1213
01:51:54,012 --> 01:51:55,539
Bow your head.

1214
01:51:57,884 --> 01:52:00,699
Father, we thank Thee
for Thy blessings...

1215
01:52:00,764 --> 01:52:02,619
and dedicate them
to Thy mercy...

1216
01:52:02,684 --> 01:52:05,717
We are about to receive...

1217
01:52:05,788 --> 01:52:07,414
Forgive us all...

1218
01:52:07,484 --> 01:52:09,491
even white trash
like Starling here...

1219
01:52:09,564 --> 01:52:12,499
and bring her
into my service, amen.

1220
01:52:14,492 --> 01:52:18,616
I have to tell you, Paul, even the
Apostle Paul couldn't have done better.

1221
01:52:18,684 --> 01:52:20,691
He hated women too.

1222
01:52:20,764 --> 01:52:24,080
May I have some wine, please?
I don't think that's a good idea.

1223
01:52:24,156 --> 01:52:25,782
Not with the morphine.

1224
01:52:25,852 --> 01:52:28,218
I think you should
eat some broth. Okay?

1225
01:52:28,284 --> 01:52:33,073
